description:
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen in the Microbiology Department for a Senior Medical Laboratory Assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties include entering patient information onto the laboratory computer system, initial processing of samples and use of automated sampling equipment. &lt;br /&gt;Previous laboratory experience is required, although some additional training will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will require NVQ level 2 in clinical care or equivalent and be prepared to make a significant contribution to the Microbiology service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good computer keyboard skills are essential. Core hours are Monday to Friday between 09.00-17.30, but flexibility is required with regular working across different shifts currently between 06.00 and 22.00 including weekends and bank holidays. Service needs are rapidly changing in response to the COVID pandemic., as our working patterns and hrs in response to this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Anita Kenyon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Microbiology Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address anita.kenyon@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01536 492678&lt;/p&gt;
